THE HUNDRED - FOOT JOURNEY
The Hundred - Foot Journey is a novel written by Richard C. Morais and published in July 2010 .
It was adapted into a feature film of the same name in 2014 .
PLOT Section::::Plot .
It is a story about how the hundred - foot distance between a new Indian restaurant and a traditional French one represents the gulf between different cultures and desires .
It focuses on the rivalry and resolution of the two restaurants and is based in Saint - Antonin - Noble - Val , France .
The book is narrated by Hassan Haji , the protagonist of the novel , who is born and raised in his family 's Indian restaurant in Mumbai , and it encompasses his journey from child to world - renowned chef .
ADAPTATION Section::::Adaptation .
On June 3 , 2013 , DreamWorks set Lasse Hallstr√∂m to direct the film The Hundred - Foot Journey , which was released on August 8 , 2014 .
Steven Spielberg produced the film with Oprah Winfrey and Juliet Blake .
